This paper deals with the traveling salesperson problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and optimization. The paper uses lift-and-project procedures, which are commonly used in optimization and linear programming. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.OC (Optimization and Control), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
